.
.

.
Das was die Weine des kleinen Garagenweinguts Arnot-Roberts aus Sonoma auszeichnet ist ihre Frische, Brillanz und der moderate Alkoholgehalt.
.
Kalifornien ist aufgrund des Klimas und Talents der Produzenten in der Lage einen komplett eigenständigen Stil zu keltern. Die Blaubeerfrucht, die herbe Würzigkeit, der Duft von schwarzen Pfefferkörnern und der köstliche Crunch am Gaumen sind einfach genial.
.
Natürlich kann dieser Stoff reifen, aber in der jetzigen Fruchtphase macht das Teil irre Trinkspass im Glas!
.
.

insta_description:
CITY OF ANGELES НА КАРАНТИНЕ
⠀
Ресторанам разрешено работать только на вынос, школы, бары, фитнес центры, кинотеатры закрыты, люди понимают серьезность ситуации и важность карантина, но город не вымер конечно, хотя на улицах стало еще меньше людей, я заметила много бегунов тк спорт залы закрыты, в нашем комплексе тоже закрыли и бассейны и джакузи. Магазины работают до 7-8 вечера, людей там становится меньше, найти можно всё, особенно если прийти пораньше, кроме заморозки и туалетной бумаги😅 чтобы люди не толпились на входе может стоять человек контролирующий поток покупателей, да ещё антисептиком на входе и выходе брызнет на ручки. Продуктовые очереди сменились на оружейные, бензин подешевел на 20%, а цены в онлайн магазинах подросли, пробок нет, смягчены правила парковки и отсрочены платежи по штрафам, воду и электричество не отключат за не уплату, а вот что на счёт рента, вопрос сложный, ведь очень много людей осталось без работы, а цены высокие. Петицию об отмене арендных выплат мы уже подписали 🤓
⠀
Прогноз не сильно радужный, ну хоть солнышко вышло, с ним как то повеселее ☀️ а ещё в Сиэтле, волонтеру сделали первую тестовую инъекцию вакцины, но даже при положительном результате, по разным оценкам понадобится 1-1.5 года чтобы вакцина стала общедоступной
⠀

The world is a scary place right now. There’s a lot I was looking forward to in the next few weeks that has been cancelled (including a trip to Bishop that was supposed to start tomorrow).
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The best thing we can do for ourselves, each other, and the world is to stay local and limit physical contact for the time being. As much as it sucks, and even though I’m working remote for the next three weeks, that means not traveling anywhere. Especially not into rural communities that don’t have the infrastructure to handle a large COVID-19 outbreak.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Other than going a bit stir crazy and getting ready to give each of my plants their own Instagram story, I am doing well. If you need anything that you think I could help with, please reach out. Let’s be there for each other right now.

accessibility_caption: Image may contain: 1 person, standing
insta_description:
Honey, I’M HOME 🏡
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Made it back to the States 🇺🇸 SAFE (healthy) and SOUND. Immediately satisfied my In n Out 🍟 and Girl Scout Cookies 🍪 cravings. Reunited with my mom, brother, and two dogs 🐶 after not seeing them for 1 YEAR 📆
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Still trying to get adjusted to this cold ass weather 🥶, driving again, the time zone differences (jet lag is real 😴), the reverse culture shock of a 1st world country, and the effects of the coronavirus pandemic 🦠
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
While I’m anxious to reunite with everyone, I understand the IMPORTANCE of self-isolating, and plan to use this time to the FULLEST. Meditation, yoga 🧘🏼‍♀️, at-home workouts, reading 📖, blogging, and working on my new business will be filling up my schedule—as well as a little Netflix binging 🍿 and QUALITY time with my family ❣️
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I look forward to sharing all the projects I’ve been working on 👩🏼‍💻, staying connected with you all through social media 📱, and finally getting together with everyone once things settle down 🚗
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This may have not been the ideal situation to come home to, but it’s important to make the best of it and remain POSITIVE and GRATEFUL. Let’s focus on the GOOD, instead of the perceived bad. Let’s get creative with our time in isolation💡, help each other out however we can 👫, and remember to be SELFLESS, not selfish 💞
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Hakuna matata,
Sierra Nicole
.

insta_description:
Rainy Day Recipe | Korean Spiced Tomato Soup | Turmeric + Olive Oil Creme | Cilantro |  #soup #rainyday #comfort #localingredients #simplicity #california #sandiego #chefslife #spiceology #truecooks #recipe 
Recipe: 👇🏽👇🏽👇🏽 Tomato soup

1 oz. evoo. 
3 oz. onion, chopped
1 tbl. garlic, chopped
1 tbl. ginger, chopped 
2 oz.gochujang, Korean chili paste
2 tsp. honey
28 oz. tomatoes, if can use San Marzano 
2 cups. vegetable broth, chicken broth 
Method: in a medium size pot lightly sweat the first 4 ingredients until tender, approx, 15 on low heat. Add remaining ingredients and cook on medium heat for 30 minutes. Remove from heat and blend smooth. Adjust heat levels and sweetness with either more Korean chili paste and honey. 
Whipped creme~ take heavy cream and add turmeric, salt + pepper, evoo and whip until small peaks are achieved. Chill and dollop on top of soup when ready. Garnish with either basil or cilantro. 🙏🏾👨🏽‍🍳

insta_description:
Today's #WorldwideWednesday Comes from San Francisco California. The legendary Gold Coast of Pacific Heights is an elite enclave on Outer Broadway known for its majestic homes, notable residents and unsurpassed views. Here, on a coveted corner lot set high above the city and the bay, this imposing 11,600± sq.ft. mansion is the foremost offering on the market in San Francisco, presenting a rare opportunity to own a custom-built residence in a world-class location with world-class views. Impressively engineered of concrete and steel and completed circa 2004, it displays quality construction, craftsmanship and refinement. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
The eminently comfortable home has six bedrooms—five en suite—seven full baths, and two half baths. Floors are clad in walnut, raw limestone and marble. High-ceilinged public spaces are airy, open, and ideal for entertaining on any scale. The centerpiece of the home is a spectacular serpentine staircase with ornate railings crafted by Italian artisans. The property features interior design by both Ken Fulk and Eric Cohler, elevator access to four levels, a secondary back staircase, smart home technology, radiant heating, two working fireplaces, hand-plastered walls, mahogany doors and windows, a four-car garage with an EV charging station, and abundant storage. Unparalleled, panoramic views unfold from the Golden Gate Bridge and the Marin Headlands, across San Francisco Bay, and all the way to the Oakland Hills, showcasing such landmarks as the Palace of Fine Arts, Alcatraz and Angel Island. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Also known as Billionaire's Row, these three tranquil blocks offer respite from busy city life yet are just blocks from the boutiques, restaurants and shops of fashionable Sacramento Street. Nearby are Julius Kahn Playground as well as the Presidio - a national park and historic district - which offers the Presidio Golf Course, miles of trails, picnic areas, museums, restaurants, Crissy Field, and Baker Beach.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
We are proud to be part of a network of over 1000 offices arounf the globe. This extraordinary property is represented by @SothebysRealty San Francisco. Click the link in our bio to learn more! ⁠⠀

insta_description:
Recreational marijuana retailers throughout several markets in the U.S. saw a dramatic spike in #sales in recent days, according to new data, an unambiguous sign that the #coronavirus #pandemic is prompting consumers to stock up on #products.
-
The run on cannabis stores may come from the fear that marijuana shops will be closed indefinitely, similar to measures taken in several states to shutter bars and restaurants.
-
According to point-of-sale data provided by Seattle-based Headset, daily sales in #California spiked 159% on #Monday over same-day sales in 2019. #Colorado and #Washington state also reported significant spikes, as shown in the chart above.
-
Year-over-year growth continues
-
Sales in #2020 have outpaced those of #2019 across all recreational marijuana markets. This is a fundamental characteristic of a growing industry.
-
But the degree to which sales over the previous weekend – and also on Monday – outperformed sales during the same time period in 2019 fell well outside the norm.
-
On average, year-over-year adult-use sales on Fridays between Jan. 10 and March 6 were up 70% in California, 9% in Colorado and 8% in Washington state.
-
The average year-over-year increase for adult-use sales on Mondays between Jan. 6 and March 9 was 71% in California, 10% in Colorado and 15% in Washington state – meaning the percent increases seen in each market on Monday, March 16, 2020, were several standard deviations beyond the norm.
-
In each market, the sales figures posted on Monday looked much more like a typical Friday, which is usually the biggest sales day of the week for retail cannabis stores.
-

We've gone curbside!!!! .

Day 2 Long Beach and we are taking beer and bread to the streets as we roll with the punches.

Yesterday was a great success but to get through these times we need community support and we are here to provide Long Beach with the best brewed and baked products available.

As we transition into delivery we start today with curbside service. If you are feeling skittish about getting out of your car we have a remote point of sale to help you out.

Want to skip the wait? We have online pre-ordering for pickup (Link in bio). We can text notify when your order is ready. Just leave a note in the order that you are requesting curbside, tell us the make and model of your vehicle and we will bring it out to you.

Store.lbbeer.com 
BREAD LAB UPDATE: @lbbread .

We are running out of bread fast daily. We have ramped up production but to garuntee you get your Bread Lab favorite loaf please preorder.

Preorder days are fulfilled on Tuesdays and Fridays and need to be  made by 4pm 3 days prior.

Go to lbbread.com to preorder and see details on pick.

Thanks so much for your support.

4 pack cans of your favorite beers will be available as soon as we can so in the meantime get a 16 oz or 32 oz can crowler to go.

We got you Long Beach.

insta_description:
In these unprecedented times of instability and stock market chaos the first thing that gets cut is discretionary spending. Yes, I mean art. It is also a perfect time to re-evaluate my vision and create something new. During uncertain times we look for security and safety. As as artist I can create the world that I desire within my work. As I scan back in history one time that sticks out as carefree and exciting was the 1950’s California Surf culture. Between the cool cars, the rebellious attitudes, and the surf music it gives a sense of calm that we need right now. I am thinking of doing some smaller works on paper with this theme. Leave a comment if interested?

insta_description:
body weight workout for y’all // I even dragged @nickpolito1 along for the ride 🙂🙃
WARM UP
- front lunge w/ rotation (alternating sides): 60 sec
- inch worm w/ 4x mtn climbers: 60 sec
- mtn climbers: 30 sec
- tempo push up (3 counts down 1 count up): 60 sec
- quick feet: 30 sec

AMRAP: 8 minute
- 10 single leg deadlift (R)
- 10 single leg deadlift (L)
- 10 double jump squat
- 10 froggers (plank to low squat) or burpees
- 10 side plank rotation to push up
- 10 high knees

CIRCUIT: 45 seconds work/15 second rest (5 rounds)
- jumping jacks
- jab cross for speed
- sumo squat w/ cross body rotation
- lateral bear crawl (2 walks R/2 walks L)
- twisted mtn climbers

This can be done literally anywhere...your bedroom, kitchen, outside, etc. — get sweating fam!

I’ve always been a sporadic person. For a lot of us, that’s an inherent part of who we are. But as we get older, our goals become defined and our to do-lists grow, and it’s easy to lose track of the sporadic and carefree nature we have when we’re young. 
Don’t let yourself lose track of that. Don’t forget the absolute freedom and power that you have. Don’t become a to do-list.  It’s okay to change plans at the last minute. It’s okay to go for a drive with no destination. It’s okay to swim in your jeans. .

insta_description:
(Reuters) - Millions of California's Bay area residents can still legally light up as cannabis facilities are exempt from a #cornonavirus lockdown that has shuttered most businesses in #SanFrancisco and nearby cities.
-
Cannabis store managers say they have lines longer than local grocery shops and waiting room only. Most staff at a dozen stores reached Tuesday evening said they were too busy to talk to Reuters.
-
"Oh man, we're flooded. As soon as people heard we were still open, they started lining up," said Anthony Barajas, the general manager of Cana Culture in #SanJose.
-
"Once all the toilet paper got sold out, they knew they needed some relief," he said.
-
#Bars, #clubs, #gyms and other businesses all closed Monday under one of the strictest orders made so far in the United States aimed at stemming the coronavirus #pandemic. Around 7 million people reside in the area affected by the orders.
-
Cannabis stores and vendors join the short list of "essential" places that can stay open along with grocery stores, pharmacies and doctors offices, the San Jose Mercury News and other media reported, citing the state's Bureau of Cannabis Control and local officials.
-
#California has more than 500 confirmed cases of coronavirus and at least 12 people have died.
-

insta_description:
Friendly reminder to slow down & be grateful✨

There’s SO much going on in the world right now. Entire cities & countries shut down, schools and places of work closed, the toilet paper shortage... 🤯 It’s easy to become anxious and focus on all the negativity surrounding you. Challenge yourself to focus on the POSITIVITY surrounding you in your day to day. What are you grateful for? Focus on gratitude for the small things ( that are now becoming the big things ) like your health, safety, food, shelter, your family being together, or even the luxury of working from home.

Challenge yourself to be grateful and let the negativity & anxiety wash away. 🤍

Pax, Somers Vineyard, Mission 2019

100% mission coming from the organically farmed Somers Vineyard in Lodi. This wine undergoes 100% whole cluster fermentation then sees 4 months of elevage in neutral French oak with an additional month in concrete after. Very interesting wine clocking in at 12.5% ABV with a pretty serious tannin structure. Pronounced spicy, floral, and savory notes with little red fruit fruit intensity. Serve with a chill and alongside carnitas on your next taco night. . . .

S O C I A L—D I S T A N C I N G😷🙅🏼‍♀️ Things are a little hectic right meow. 🥴
If the story you’re living in has “can’t” in it and focusing on all the things you cannot do..
Take a moment for a quick mindset shift and focus on...⬇️⬇️
+ relationships are not cancelled.💕
.
+ love is not cancelled!
.
+ catch up on reading, or other tasks you’ve put off (whatever you complain you don’t have time for normally, take advantage 😉)
.
+ declutter closets, or other spaces in your home you’ve neglected (that junk drawer with sauce packets and randos) Marie Kondo, anyone?✨
.
+ think of quarantine as an adult snow day 🤪
.
+ FaceTime or google hangouts for watching shows together or even enjoying meals together. Have your own virtual happy hour.🍷
.
+ give yourself permission for a movie marathon or Netflix binge📽🍿
.
+ begin Game of Thrones if you haven’t😉
.
+ free resources on YouTube and other virtual platforms for yoga, workouts, new hobbies.🧘🏼‍♀️🏋️‍♀️
.
+ online museum tours 💻
.
+ write letters, create art for individuals in nursing homes who aren’t allowed to have visitors during this time.💌
.
+ take a deep breath and lean on others during this time. Technology allows us to virtually do pretty much anything.📱💻
.

Making the decision to change your life’s trajectory was tough. I toyed around with the idea to join the military because of my friends and the quality of life they had! .
It took me about a year to get enough courage to walk into a recruiting station and I am so glad I did. I joined the Army 15 years ago as Military Police (31b). I currently make around 7,500 a month and can provide my family all the amenities that they could want! .
When people ask me what I love about the Army I always say JOB SECURITY!

My recommendation to everyone is to talk with a recruiter to get all the information. Then look up that information on google/YouTube. 
If you want to talk about my Army story I will be more than happy to tell you about my time.

insta_description:
So important right now.

Mental health care simply doesn't have the funding that it needs and many vulnerable groups(minorities, the #lgbtq community, and those in poverty) don't have access to good mental health care or treatment at all. This can be devastating—as proper treatment of severe mental illness can be the difference between life and death.

During times of crisis like what we are going through right now, I am actually encouraged by what I am seeing in terms of mental health professionals doing to make care accessible through alternative methods like #telemedicine, but we need to be diligent in ensuring that everyone at risk within the mental health community can receive help if they need it right now.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

insta_description:
This engagement shoot was everything! 💍

And I’m so glad we got it done right before the crazy. To say that this is ill-timed would be quite the understatement, not that there’s ever a right time for a pandemic... 🙄

These were going to be the last two months I continued to shoot until I go on maternity leave (yup, baby #2 is due in early July!). My last hoorah is the giveaway. Now more then ever, I want to do this giveaway for the people of my community. To bring hope and joy in an uncertain time. To give back when finances are a little scary.

I’m still booking portrait/elopement sessions now till early May. After that, the plan is to return Nov 2020.

A lot of people’s schedules have cleared, so feel free to reach out!

🇺🇲 Shawn Serrano aka Shawn Wasabi, Music Producer and Dj born 1994 in Salinas, California, USA.

Artist: @shawnwasabi

In 2013, Shawn Wasabi started producing music after his friend left the Midi Fighter 3D at his house. Since then, he has uploaded his live mashups, which have all garnered millions of views on YouTube. In 2015, he released "Marble Soda", using a Midi Fighter 64. It contains samples from 153 different tracks and sounds. The video for the song reached 1 million views on YouTube within 48 hours of being uploaded. In 2016, he was nominated for the Breakthrough Artist award at the 6th Streamy Awards. In 2017, he released "Spicy Boyfriend". In that year, he also released "Otter Pop", which featured guest vocalist Hollis. The Faderplaced it at number 27 on the "101 Best Songs of 2017" list. In 2018, he released "Squeez", which featured guest vocalist Raychel Jay. The song was included on Paper's "10 Songs You Need to Start Your Weekend Right" list, as well as The Fader's "20 Best New Pop Songs Right Now" list.

We are reaching out to our valued clients during this unprecedented COVID-19 pandemic to assure you that The Parkman Law Firm safely remains open with our staff transitioned to working in remote locations to conform to government mandates and maintain social distancing. We are committed to taking the appropriate steps to mitigate the spread of the virus. We will be working remotely until at least April 3, 2020, pending updates received from government officials. Our staff working remotely is preemptive and none of one has reported any exposure or infection from the virus. ⁠
⁠
You will still be able to contact The Parkman Law Firm as you normally do by phone and email during our regular business hours, from 9:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. ⁠
⁠
To our clients with open litigation cases filed in the California Superior Court, the court has announced a suspension of all non-emergency services at least until April 3, 2020. This essentially will halt all activities on your court case. All hearings and dates previously set in your open case have been postponed and no new dates have yet been set. Our firm’s staff will continue to monitor this situation and will provide you statuses on your case as time progresses.⁠
⁠
To our business owner, employer, and employee clients we realize there are many questions surrounding the economic slowdown, business closures, human resources, and wages. We have been monitoring the new legislation being proposed and are available to answer your questions on the state of the current law and upcoming new laws regarding this issue. If you have urgent and important questions on these matters, we are ready and available to assist you.⁠
⁠
We urge our clients to remain positive, calm, and healthy while we navigate this global crisis. Together, we will emerge stronger and wiser. ⁠

insta_description:
I hope you are all doing well during these crazy times.  Social media says business owners have to post every day to stay relevant.  Its hard during times like this to find the motivation, and it feels a little strange to try and post about photography and tips etc when you're going through a pandemic. But the show must go on, 
Pro Tip: Make sure your wedding photographer and other professionals are insured, many are facing the tough decision of cancelling their weddings or pushing the date back which is so sad, but an ensured team will be ideal in situations like these. Always ask your wedding professionals if they are insured or their policy for rescheduling before booking. 
Also please check on your small business owner friends, because this is really a hard time, filled with uncertainty about where or when our next gigs or customers will come from. We cannot rely on our employers to give us PTO because we are our employers.  Also shout out to all the medical, safety, human services workers, hospitality and grocery store workers who are still working diligently to provide quality care for all of us in quarantine, and teachers who are still putting together lesson plans and virtual classrooms while their students are driving their parents crazy at home. You all are the real MVP's. It'll get better you guys.

insta_description: It’s Weathered Souls Wednesday, my dudes! I’m featuring a beer from a kickass TX brewery with one of the funniest beer names I’ve seen: Game, Blouses. Why don’t you purify yourself in the waters of Lake Minnetonka? 🎸🟪🌧😆 Loads of bourbon barrel, bourbon vanilla beans on the nose, mushy-ripe banana with just a whisper of marshmallow. Smoky vanilla on the palate followed by charred stave. I am happy that the marshmallow doesn’t do much more than exhibit a shadow on the palate. Smoky throughout. Dark chocolate, charred Barrel on the finish. After warming a bit, it becomes dark chocolate hot cocoa with a nice creamy and marshmallow balance. Upon oxidation, the finish flourishes with slightly sweet, nutty, buttercream, dark chocolate, and decadent bourbon. 🤤🍫🥜 Shoutout to @beer_reviewer for the bottle - best bottle I’ve received from you, mate. 📦 Which one of your local breweries have you supported during this crisis? 🤔 #weatheredsoulsbrewing #gameblouses #barrelaged #stout #texasbeer #supportlocal #supportsmallbusiness #beermail #beer #ale #bière #cerveja #beertography #craftbeer #ilovebeer #instabeer #beergeek #beersnob #beerpics #craftist #puravida #beerporn #craftbeer #losangeles #socal #california #lbc #longbeach #craftstitution

insta_description:
Poetry Thoughts | Photography
————————————————
Green sceneries engraved in my heart 
Waterfall swimming in an empty cart 
Drops of water walking on a dead leaf 
Humanity erased happiness and fell for grief 
A disguised love wrapped in a piece of ice 
Melting in the eyes of human race 
Tomorrow was laughing on the surface of the Earth
Trying to breathe the false truth of fresh air 
Deep down lived the devil 
Dark, cold blooded , and evil
You are the child of the universe the silence said
I screamed loud and went to bed 
I was scared of the unknown 
What was complete is now torn 
Earth forgive me I have to leave 
I can’t survive with endless screams 
I was looking for kindness in every face 
Wake me up when tomorrow finds its pace 
I have to sleep for many years 
And wipe away my dry tears 
People are controlled by their selfish needs 
Your health is defined by what you eat 
It’s time to let go your ego 
Kindness is calling listen to the echo 
I wish to live in a eco friendly world 
I wish the voice of the voiceless will soon be heard ————————————————-

.

accessibility_caption: Image may contain: sky, night and outdoor
insta_description:
Vincent Thomas Bridge • I was in awe that my camera caught this amount of color in the sky. You can’t see in it, as Instagram shrunk down the photo, but I even captured some stars. I was like, what are these white dots in the sky? OH! Stars! I haven’t done much night photography, but now I want to go capture more nightscapes!

As I practice social distancing, I have been noticing the amount of people that say hi to me when I’m walking my dog in the evening. I think they feel weird by the 6 ft distance, so they say hi to compensate the awkwardness. On my walks, I normally avoid people because I’m a woman walking at night. I don’t know you. I don’t know your intentions. It’s dark. Before, it used to be about Milah being skeptical around people, but as she got used to people, I just got accustomed to being wanted to be left alone when I’m walking at night.  Anyway, as we take time for ourselves, pay more attention to the changes in behavior between others. It’s interesting to watch.

Passou a menina mais linda 🙋🏻‍♀️ tomei coragem e comecei a falar 💃🏻 Nossa, nossa, assim você me mata 🥵 - ai se eu te pego, michael telò 🎤

The prettiest girl passed by & I got the courage to start to talk to her 💋 wow wowo you kill me 😏

FUN FACT I speak Portuguese! Azorean Portuguese specifically which is slightly different than PT and way different than Brazilian Portuguese! My nationality is Portuguese (&&Argentinian/kinda Italian-long story) 🇵🇹🇦🇷🇭🇺 Growing up we visited the Azores (São Miguel) often since my papa is from there ☺️ It wasn’t until I was 17 that I started speaking “fluently” - to each their own as to what that means, I had *married* someone who only spoke Portuguese sooo I think I was okay at it - and in the last few years, I’ve lost so much of it!

I am going to Portugal and the Azores (Italy too!) in June, so far 🙏🏻 and I’m brushing up and relearning. Portuguese Lab on YouTube is a great resource. So if you’re a Portuguese speaker hi hi and if not, that’s still cool 😎

insta_description:
Herbal formulas.
These formulas are in pill form so no stinky, hard to drink decoctions. (anyone who was forced to drink these as a kid knows what I'm talking about!)
I have a good supply, but am limited by my source, who is being inundated by extra orders. It's been shown that certain TCM formulas were used in China, in conjunction with Western medicine to help alleviate symptoms (such as weakness, cough and lunch function). These are not a cure for  COVID19 or even the flu. But rather a way to support immunity and any symptoms you may have. 
Have other issues? Chronic back pain? Stress and anxiety? Headaches? Menstrual pains? 
I've got herbs for that too! These are a great complement to acupuncture treatments, but can be used as a great stand alone therapy!
I'm doing herbal consultations by phone or email. Please email me at sophia@embrace-acu.com to schedule a consult. We can figure out payment over the phone and herb drop off/pick up if you are local. 
Got any other questions regarding acupuncture and its benefits? I'm conducting free (up to 15 mins) phone consultations! Email me to schedule something!

Stay safe and healthy!

accessibility_caption: Image may contain: food
insta_description:
Una leggenda sulla creazione dei brownies è quella di Bertha Palmer, una mondana di Chicago, il cui marito possedeva il Palmer House Hotel. Un giorno nel 1893, chiese ad un pasticcere di creare un dolce adatto alle donne che frequentavano il Chicago World's Columbian Exposition. Chiese poi che il dolce fosse simile ad un piccolo pezzo di torta e che si potesse consumare anche durante un pranzo al sacco. 
Il risultato fu chiamato Palmer House Brownie, che conteneva noci ed era ricoperto di glassa alle albicocche.

Tutt'oggi al Palmer House Hotel viene servito un dolce ai clienti che si dice venga fatto usando la stessa ricetta originale.
Il nome fu dato poco dopo il 1893, ma non venne usato da libri di cucina o riviste dell'epoca.

Una torta al cioccolato tagliata a pezzetti che arrecano tanto piacere e un color marrone da fare invidia!

Un consiglio: preparateli per la colazione e la vostra giornata non potrà che migliorare 🥛

2020 Ready

What a great time. Many major distractions cut off. No new programming being made. A giant pause. Nature is being rejuvenated. The toxins are being quarantined. What a time to dive into self. You should be surrounded by the people most important to you. Great time to get to know them.  No sports. Men are dying out there and new men will be reborn. Time to convert that time and energy into self. Time to grow up. Time to heal. Time to be creative. Times like this put things in perspective and how we prioritize them. How we value connection and how we have abused these privileges. No place to escape now. No bars, no major gatherings. If you are alone it’s ok. You have probably been trying to find someone to no avail, now you get to date yourself and see what’s up. You should not be bad company to yourself, if you are this is the perfect time to look into that. No time for excuses. We should all come out if this kinder. We should all begin to appreciate things we have taken for granted, people we have taken for granted. Have fun with your children. Create new good habits. Exercise and take care of each other. insta_description:
Today marks 3 years with The Disney Company! 🎉 Feels weird not celebrating at work today. I truly miss doing what I do and seeing my work family. Having this time off truly allows us to reflect on our every day “normal” lives. I constantly think to myself, ‘How lucky am I? How lucky am I to create happiness and make magic for so many people each and every day? How lucky am I to be surrounded by an amazingly talented creative team who sees my potential and supports my goals? How lucky am I to work in entertainment and support myself and my family at the end of the day?’ Then I remember...it’s not luck. It took years of determination, dedication, and Faith aka Faith, Trust, and Pixie Dust ✨ 
Year 3 was incredible. I had no idea what was in store in the beginning, but I opened my heart to God’s plan. At the end of 2018, I just experienced one of the roughest audition seasons. It was tough, but I collected that energy and put it towards my continued training and auditions. Keeping an open and positive mindset, Year 3 brought many new and amazing opportunities I couldn’t even imagine at the beginning of the year.
Now...we chill. We wait. We work on our craft. We pray and hope for a brighter tomorrow. We help each other and lift one another up. We open our arms to new opportunities. We embrace the unknown. I have no idea what Year 4 will bring, but I know with a solid team next to me...we can do anything. As Walt said, “It’s kind of fun to do the impossible.” ❤️

insta_description:
Rate the design from 1/10? “Vespertine” by @ericowenmoss in #California #USA / 2016.

Moss contrasted Mendelsohn’s work with the “swoopy Maya stuff” so many architects produce today. “There’s a danger that the advent of Maya and Rhino and CATIA and all of this [technology] produces generic kinds of buildings,” he said. “The power of the tools is dictating the design content.” Instead, said Moss, the architect’s tools, whether the Bauhaus-era parallel rule or today’s digital modeling systems, should be a means to rather than the end of design. “I want to argue that architecture is still personal—it still has the aspect of Mendelsohn in the trenches—and that it’s important that architecture not simply be a manifestation of the tools that are being used,” he said. “It’s not the plane that’s flying the people, but the people are flying the plane.” Architect: @ericowenmoss 
Location: California, USA 🇺🇸 Photo by @jeffed_up

Siempre nos complace responder todas sus inquietudes y que queden claras :) Empecemos a responder algunas de las preguntas que nos hacen ....
Work&travel 🇺🇸 ( viajar y trabajar en 🇺🇸 es un programa creado por el departamento de los Estados Unidos que tiene como objetivo principal el intercambio cultural entre estudiantes universitarios de diferentes partes del 🌍 la visa requerida es la J1 intercambio cultural (la cual es otorgada por la duración del programa) . Nuestros empleadores proveen el Housing 🙈👌😉 Algunos requisitos son tener nivel de inglés básico-conversacional, tener de 18-29 años al momento de aplicar y ser estudiante universitario 👩‍💻👨‍💻. Cabe resaltar que cada país cuenta con fechas específicas para realizar el programa, las fechas autorizadas para estudiantes costarricenses son entre el 01 Diciembre y 30 Marzo......
Esperamos que tengan un poco claro la información del programa😀✈️🌏🇺🇸♥️🇨🇷

insta_description: Feeling back to myself more and more lately🖤 @asoph_official When the results finally start to show through my reaction was.....WHAT WASIT?! (And lower belly😜) Guys I am just happy because I’ve had to make some dedicated changes to work off some of the extra weight I’ve gained. I’ve been making small, healthy, lifestyle changes for the past 6 months leading up to this point. But the last 6-8 weeks is where I’ve seen the most change. Here are some of the more recent changes I’ve made! 1) 5 weeks ago I cut out soda completely. 2) 4 weeks I cut out Starbucks completely and switched to at home coffees. 3)I started using @alexandrashappybody plan 3 weeks ago after seeing the success of so many others. Yes she’s my friend so the point was also to support her, however her workout videos have really jumpstarted and helped kick me into shape! I’ve been doing her videos in addition to my own cardio & weight lifting / core routines. It’s been about 3 years that I’ve gone off the road with having a dedicated, healthy lifestyle and gym routine! One thing I’ve struggled through the past 2 weeks is not comparing myself to others, and by others I mean MYSELF as well. Almost 5 years ago I was 110lbs, and 3 years ago I was 150-160lbs(my normal weight). Right now I am 174lbs!!! Its not about the amount of weight either, it’s about the lifestyle you are living. I recognize where I was mentally and physically at those other times in my life as well and have had to see how I can make the changes and get back to where I am just feeling overall happy & healthy. Your body changes with life, and that’s ok! Accept it and continue that change. I had to share because despite everything that’s going on in the outside world, I use Instagram as a way of communication and this is something I have been feeling proud about! I don’t usually share when I am truly proud of myself either, but this journey is one that you have all been on with me! Feel free to comment or DM with any questions! Also learning how to adapt to not going to the gym during this time. Feel free to share your healthy hacks! -Sav

insta_description:
It’s California poppy season, one of my favorite times of the year!  Try to imagine the hillsides just glowing orange with beautiful poppies.  I’d never really seen poppies until I moved to California.  Poppies are cheery and happy and a bit mystical.  They make me smile.
🏃🏼‍♀️
I’ve got some simple goals during Shelter in Place.  I plan to get outside every day.  I plan to exercise at least an hour a day.  Ideally, I can exercise outside!  I may ride my bicycle or run or hike.  Even a walk would help break up the monotony of being stuck in the house for 3 weeks.  And without a daily commute or 8 hours a day of clients, I’ve got plenty of time on my hands.
🏃🏼‍♀️
My emotions keep zooming back and forth.  I’m very scared for my future.  After 18 years as a bike fitter, I don’t know what else I could do with my life that would make me happy.  I’m trying to relax and not overthink it, but all small business owners are taking a hit right now.  I guess only time will tell.
🏃🏼‍♀️
A new catch phrase I’ve noticed this week is career “pivot,” meaning how to adapt and change direction while still maintaining connection to your previous career.  I honestly don’t know what that is for me.  Maybe I’m being stubborn, but I absolutely love what I do and I don’t want to do something else.  But I’m going to challenge myself to be creative and look at other possibilities.....as soon as I’m done freaking out.
🏃🏼‍♀️
What do you do for a living?  How has your job been impacted?  If you had to do something else, what would that be?
.
.
.
.
.

accessibility_caption: Image may contain: drink
insta_description:
This is what I love — the esoteric, outside the box, “didn’t know it existed” type of stuff. Enter @lolawines Malvasia Bianca, St. Helena, Napa Valley 2018. Vinified from a 4-acre parcel of 45-year-old vines in northern St. Helena, Winemaker Seth Cripe has created one of the most delicious small production white wines in the Valley🍷

While achieving ripeness can be somewhat of an easy feat here in the Valley, the Malvasia is vertically trained to manage vigor and large clusters. Come harvest time, grapes are picked at low PH and around 22 brix, in an effort to produce a lean crisp white wine that represents the purity of the vineyard and varietal🍷

Once the grapes are brought in, 70% are whole cluster pressed with that juice undergoing a native cool fermentation to dryness in neutral oak barrels. The other 30% is fermented on the skins and pulp, in an effort to add complexity and texture on the palate. The wine is racked once at bottling and has minimal S02 additions of under 35ppm total from harvest to bottling. Bottling is both unfined and unfiltered🍷

The end result is a vibrant and fresh white wine with intense aromatics of passionfruit, nectarine, peach, and apricot. The palate is weighty and textural, but carries with it a backbone of acidity that carries the wine through on the finish. It is truly a delightful and delicious fermented beverage. 124 cases produced. BTG at @pressnapavalley🍷
.
.
.

.

insta_description: Back in Mannheim. 🏡 Heute bin ich nach einem Monat endlich wieder zu Hause-Hause in Mannheim angekommen. Auf der einen Seite hab ich große Vorfreude, heute wieder in meinem eigenen Bett zu schlafen, auf der anderen Seite bin ich echt nur baff von all dem, was grad abgeht. Ich war eben einkaufen. Kein Klopapier mehr in 4 Läden. Aber gut, das ist ja nichts Neues. 🤗 Viel schlimmer finde ich aber, wie rücksichtslos manche Menschen sind. Ja, man soll und darf gern noch in Kleingruppen (bis zu 5 Leuten) an die frische Luft gehen, aber ich habe grad so viele Großgruppen auf der Straße gesehen. Unverantwortlich und für mich unbegreiflich. Bitte liebe Leute, haltet euch an die Anweisungen und trefft euch nicht zu 10. am Marktplatz auf’n Eis oder zu 15. im Park zum Trichter-Saufen.  Danke. Und nun will ich nicht nicht mehr aufregen. Imaginäre Umarmungen gehen raus an alle! ♥️🙏🏼 Dieses Bild hat übrigens meine wundervolle Schwester @vanessamona in LA von mir gemacht. Vermissung ist groß!

Since I've been a child, I have looked ahead; some call it "having my head in the clouds", but I've come to learn forward thinking gives me hope, motivation, and helps get me through some of the more unpleasant parts of life.

I'm going to start a new series titled "Where We Will Go", focusing on places that I (and hopefully you too) would like to visit once everything has settled and it is advised to travel for leisure again.

I'll be uploading photos from my favorite destinations and inviting people in the local hospitality, entertainment, food service, and tourism industry industry in these locations to share with us what makes them special and to tell my followers why we all should come visit them when we can.

So many of us are affected by what is currently going on in the world, especially local businesses relying on the tourism industry. And if we can't physically be with them now, we can start planning how we can be with them in the near future. But I can't do it without you!

If you have any friends/family/ colleagues that would like to be featured, let me know; hotels, cafes, bakeries, tour guides, restaurants, you name it! I want to showcase them all. I've tagged a few businesses and friends that I currently have stock photos for, but please feel free to send more my way!  My first destination will be the #SanDiego #California area.

insta_description:
With everything going on right now I’ve been trying to keep my son busy by doing a different activity with him every day. Today we made play dough from scratch. It was so easy and I can’t lie, even I had fun with it 😜 stay safe everyone 🙏🏼 and just think of this as more time to bond with your loved ones ❤️🧡💚💙 (INGREDIENTS) 
1 cup flour
2 tsp cream of tartar
1/2 cup salt
1 tbsp cooking oil Olive oil or vegetable oil
1 cup water
food coloring 
In a large bowl, combine all of your dry ingredients (flour, salt, cream of tartar) and mix well. -Mix food coloring with your water first. Then add the vegetable oil and water with food coloring to a large pot. Mix together. -Add the dry ingredients to your pot and mix well. -Cook over low to medium heat until the dough starts to form and becomes dry -Once it starts to form a ball together and looks fully cooked, take off the heat. Let the dough cool first before touching. -
Once cool, knead the dough for 5 minutes to make the dough soft.

Now that you’re done making your playdough, get out some cookie cutters and have fun making shapes! We also like using rolling pins and stamps to play with our playdough.

insta_description:
Finding the light. 🌞
Today I shed my first tears for what’s happening in the world. The mix of emotions went something like this:
* Sadness for my friends and family losing work as shops close, festivals are cancelled, music tours come to a halt, travel restrictions are implemented, bars and restaurants empty out, yoga studios close, hairdressers hang up their scissors, etc etc.
* Hope as I see so many magical people figuring out ways to bring a little light into our homes right now.
* Anger as I see others ignoring what’s happened in Italy and in Paris, and now in San Francisco, Seattle, NYC and New Orleans for example. I’m disgusted that people continue to go on as if they don’t have to participate collectively in flattening the curve.
* Relief after talking to the guy servicing my car — when I told him I was practicing quarantine and wouldn’t be coming in to get it he said “baby (in a way only New Orleanians can say “baby”), don’t you worry about something like a car, you take care of you and yours right now.” My head literally fell to the table when I hung up from that call.

_
And in all of that, I feel lucky. I can work from home, my partner is here with me. We have food and shelter and a warm bed and sunshine and each other. I am often called an “eternal optimist” — I live to create high vibes and hold space for others. And I suppose I share this, because truly, we’re all going to cycle through these emotions. We’re all going to experience this differently, but the more we can meet this shadow the world is facing collectively head on, the better. 🌗
_
It’s not lost on me that the Spring equinox is upon us. Spring is a time of rebirth and awakenings as the Earth rises from the cold into new life. Let’s all practice rising, waking up, and facing the light in a new way. Love you all! xx ~ Andi // 📷: @elle.hendrix #mystication #joshuatree

insta_description:
How are you doing under quarantine? Better question, what are you doing?! Fortunately I already worked from home so my routine hasn’t changed much. However I have been trying to stay home more than usual, I hadn’t left the house since Saturday until today as I had important errands to run. -

Anyways, I’m always wondering what my next meal will be, quarantine or not. Anyone that knows me knows that I hate to waste a meal on something I didn’t enjoy. So as I’m limiting my visits to the store, I was starting to be disappointed at thinking my dinner would be another soup, lentils or pasta. (Although pasta is my favorite!) Fortunately I had some frozen oysters from @lidlbulgaria and immediately fried oyster tacos came to mind!!
-

I know, I just posted a tacos recipe but this one is different yet just as delicious. After making my tortillas, I ran my frozen oysters under lukewarm water for 1 minute and then dried them off. Then I dipped them in whisked eggs, rolled them in flour and pan fried them once the pan was hot. -

To roast the chickpeas and get them crunchy (I’m obsessed with chickpeas lately) , you must blot them with a paper towel before drizzling olive oil on them. Blotting the extra liquid helps them get the crisp, otherwise they’ll just steam in the oven. -

Once the oysters and chickpeas are ready, assemble with whatever you like! I chose red cabbage for color, avocado, yogurt and hot sauce! After tonight’s tacos, my husband named me the tortilla master 😂😂 he needs to go to Mexico! Or even just California 😉 -

What are your favorite tacos? Fish? Carne asada? Al pastor? Vegetarian?

記念すべき誕生日のプレゼントとして、今月末に彼の好きな電車でショートトリップに行く予定でした🚃

実家の両親も呼んでお祝いするはずでしたが、新幹線が運休になり、東京の家族だけのお祝いとなりました。
そして、今回もまた自然の脅威によって彼のお祝いは狂わされてしまい…😢
ほんとに可哀想すぎる。
学校でお祝いしてもらいことも叶わない😭
どうすることもできないけど、一刻も早く事態が落ち着くことを願うのみです🙏

でも、子供はほとんどいない…。
なんとも寂しい。
＊

This video was filmed with a #Nikon mirrorless camera, the Z50, which is supposed to be the perfect camera for on the go vlogging and photography! At the end of this video I share my first impressions on this camera, so stick around and remember to share your thoughts as well!⁣
